      "id": "df8cc3ac-043f-4bdc-a35f-d40261c2a961",
      "name": "Sticky Note1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Create Zoho Invoice from Airtable Data \u2014 Upload to Dropbox & QuickBooks\n\nThis workflow automates the full invoicing pipeline: triggered by a webhook from Airtable, it pulls invoice data, validates required fields, creates an invoice in Zoho, fetches the PDF, uploads it to Dropbox, and generates a QuickBooks Desktop .iif file \u2014 with Slack notifications at key steps.\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Receives a webhook trigger containing an Airtable record ID\n2. Configures Zoho API settings, then fetches the invoice record from Airtable\n3. Simultaneously checks for associated time entries, expenses, and mileage records\n4. Validates that required fields (customer ID and line items) are present \u2014 stops with an error if not\n5. Creates the invoice in Zoho via API with all assembled line items\n6. Validates the Zoho response \u2014 stops with a Slack alert if the API call fails\n7. Fetches the finalized invoice PDF from Zoho\n8. Uploads the PDF invoice to Dropbox\n9. Generates a QuickBooks Desktop .iif file from the invoice data\n10. Uploads the .iif file to Dropbox for QuickBooks Desktop import\n11. Updates the Airtable invoice record to reflect completion\n12. Sends a Slack confirmation on success\n\n\n**Setup Requirements:**\n- Connect Airtable OAuth2 and update the base/table IDs in the \"Get Invoice,\" \"Get Time Entries,\" \"Get Expenses,\" and \"Update Invoice\" nodes\n- Connect Zoho Invoice OAuth2 and confirm your Organization ID in the \"ZoHo Settings\" node\n- Connect Dropbox OAuth2 and set your target folder paths in both Upload nodes\n- Connect Slack OAuth2 and set your notification channel in both Slack nodes\n- Configure your webhook trigger URL in whatever system fires the workflow (e.g., an Airtable automation)\n\n\n**Line Item Handling:**\n- Workflow checks independently for time entries, expenses, and mileage\n- Each type uses a Code node to emit an empty placeholder if no records exist \u2014 this keeps the Merge node from deadlocking when one or more categories are absent\n- All three branches merge before invoice creation, ensuring complete line items regardless of which categories have data\n\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- Missing required fields (customer ID or line items): workflow stops and sends a Slack alert\n- Zoho API failure: workflow stops and sends a separate Slack alert with response details\n- All stops use n8n's native Stop and Error node for visibility in execution logs\n\n\n**Note:** Workflow is triggered on-demand via webhook \u2014 it does not run on a schedule. One webhook call = one invoice processed.",
        "height": 1056,
        "width": 672
      },
